<p>I trade my products for other people&#8217;s products and services. The advertised retail cost of our products and our services are the values we use for each exchange. Taxes and shipping must be paid in cash, they can&#8217;t be bartered.</p>
<p>Unfortunately my landlord won&#8217;t accept anything except real money for his rent payment. And utility companies won&#8217;t either.</p>
<p>I would accept bitcoins if I could use them to pay my store rent or convert them into cash, but, not until then.</p>
