        </div>
        <div id="dsq-comment-body-235117" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-235117" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>The real issue with online currencies is transaction costs. The typical fee is 3%, but more for small transactions. It might be 35 cents plus somewhere from 2.2-2.9%. But on a $10 deal that 35 cents is 3.5% on top of the other 2.5% for a total of 6%. And on a $5 deal it&#8217;s nearly 10% fee.</p>
<p>We need an online currency system that significantly reduces transaction costs, especially for small deals. Dwolla might get there. Not sure if BitCoin addresses this problem.</p>
</div>
        </div>

    <ul class="children">
    <li class="comment odd alt depth-2" id="dsq-comment-267048">
        <div id="dsq-comment-header-267048" class="dsq-comment-header">
